                        <p class="mb-5">Random-access memory (RAM) is a form of computer data storage that stores data and machine code currently being used. A random-access memory device allows data items to be read or written in almost the same amount of time irrespective of the physical location of data inside the memory.</p>
                        <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg rounded-pill portfolio-modal-dismiss" href="#"><i class="fa fa-shopping-cart"></i> Shop</a>
                        <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg rounded-pill portfolio-modal-dismiss" href="#">
